FuncDef:
The priority command enables antilocking PFC for a specified priority queue.
The undo priority command disables antilocking PFC for a specified priority queue. The priority command enables antilocking PFC for a specified priority queue. The undo priority command disables antilocking PFC for a specified priority queue. By default, antilocking PFC is not enabled for any priority queue. This command is supported only on the CE6885-SAN.

ParaDef.Info:
Specifies the priority.
The value is an integer ranging from 0 to 7.
